{"key":"processedPost-10139667","value":{"id":10139667,"first":10138533,"last":10139677,"when":1239337249,"utime":"04/10/09 07:20 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Noobey said:</b><br />What i thought i could do RR is calibrate my analog hyg by setting it next to the digital hyg. Let them sit for 30 min, then set the analog to what the digital hyg says.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Nope.&nbsp; Use the towel method if you're growing mushrooms.&nbsp; If you're keeping cigars in a humidor, use the salt method.&nbsp; No hygrometer is accurate beyond about 1/3 of it's scale.&nbsp; You must calibrate in the area you're going to be operating.&nbsp; Digital hygrometers are crap.&nbsp; I can't say it enough.&nbsp; If you have $300 to spend, you can get one that isn't too bad until you spray it with mist or you don't harvest until after spores have plugged the transducer, and <i>then</i> it's crap just like the cheap ones.<br />RR","title":"Re: Calibration Method?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}